lbi-1919-142785-0029 LEMON JUICE MAY BE ADDED AT PLEASURE
lbi-1919-142785-0030 MODE PUT THE WHOLE OF THE INGREDIENTS INTO A BOTTLE AND LET IT REMAIN FOR A FORTNIGHT IN A WARM PLACE OCCASIONALLY SHAKING UP THE CONTENTS
lbi-1919-142785-0031 THEY OUGHT TO BE TAKEN UP IN THE AUTUMN AND WHEN DRIED IN THE HOUSE WILL KEEP TILL SPRING
lbi-1919-142785-0032 ADD THE WINE AND IF NECESSARY A SEASONING OF CAYENNE WHEN IT WILL BE READY TO SERVE
lbi-1919-142785-0033 NOTE THE WINE IN THIS SAUCE MAY BE OMITTED AND AN ONION SLICED AND FRIED OF A NICE BROWN SUBSTITUTED FOR IT
lbi-1919-142785-0034 SIMMER FOR A MINUTE OR TWO AND SERVE IN A TUREEN
lbi-1919-142785-0035 SUFFICIENT TO SERVE WITH FIVE OR SIX MACKEREL
lbi-1919-142785-0036 VARIOUS DISHES ARE FREQUENTLY ORNAMENTED AND GARNISHED WITH ITS GRACEFUL LEAVES AND THESE ARE SOMETIMES BOILED IN SOUPS ALTHOUGH IT IS MORE USUALLY CONFINED IN ENGLISH COOKERY TO THE MACKEREL SAUCE AS HERE GIVEN
lbi-1919-142785-0037 FORCEMEAT FOR COLD SAVOURY PIES
lbi-1919-142785-0038 POUND WELL AND BIND WITH ONE OR TWO EGGS WHICH HAVE BEEN PREVIOUSLY BEATEN AND STRAINED
lbi-1919-142785-0039 ILLUSTRATION MARJORAM
lbi-1919-142785-0040 IT IS A NATIVE OF PORTUGAL AND WHEN ITS LEAVES ARE USED AS A SEASONING HERB THEY HAVE AN AGREEABLE AROMATIC FLAVOUR
lbi-1919-142785-0041 MODE MIX ALL THE INGREDIENTS WELL TOGETHER CAREFULLY MINCING THEM VERY FINELY BEAT UP THE EGG MOISTEN WITH IT AND WORK THE WHOLE VERY SMOOTHLY TOGETHER
lbi-1919-142785-0042 SUFFICIENT FOR A MODERATE SIZED HADDOCK OR PIKE
lbi-1919-142785-0043 NOW BEAT AND STRAIN THE EGGS WORK THESE UP WITH THE OTHER INGREDIENTS AND THE FORCEMEAT WILL BE READY FOR USE
